<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>CSS</title>
    <style>
         p,h3{
            color:darkgoldenrod;
        }
        #id_selector{
            color: black;
            background-color: aliceblue;
            text-decoration: underline;
            text-align: center;
        }
        .class_selcetor{
            color: rgb(0, 30, 255);
            background-color: rgb(113, 172, 206);
            text-decoration:dotted;
            text-align:left;
        }
/* This will change h2 in div only */
       div h2{ 
        background-color: dimgray;
       }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
<h1 id="id_selector"> This is underline and id slector example</h1>
<h2 style="background-image:url(data:image/png;base64,);"> Welcome</h2>
 <div class="class_selcetor">
        <h2>Section One</h2>
        <p>This box uses the <span class="highlight">class_selcetor</span> class.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="class_selcetor">
        <h2>Section Two</h2>
        <p>This box also uses the <span class="highlight">class_selcetor</span> class because classes are reusable!</p>
    </div>
<p> Hello friends</p>
<h3> How are you?</h3>
</body>
</html>
